A BILL
To amend section 2901.05 of the Revised Code to 1
enact the Self-Defense Protection Act to create 2
a pretrial procedure for a person asserting 3
self-defense, defense of another, or defense of 4
that person's property. 5
BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF OHIO:
Section 1. That section 2901.05 of the Revised Code be 6
amended to read as follows: 7
Sec. 2901.05. (A) Every person accused of an offense is 8
presumed innocent until proven guilty beyond a reasonable doubt, 9
and the burden of proof for all elements of the offense is upon 10
the prosecution. The burden of going forward with the evidence 11
of an affirmative defense, and the burden of proof, by a 12
preponderance of the evidence, for an affirmative defense other 13
than self-defense, defense of another, or defense of the 14
accused's residence presented as described in division (B)(1) of 15
this section, is upon the accused. 16
(B)(1) A person is allowed to act in self-defense, defense 17
of another, or defense of that person's residence. 18
(a) A person who is accused of an offense that involved 19

