(2) Subject to division (B)(3) of this section, a person 68
is presumed to have acted in self-defense or defense of another 69
when using defensive force that is intended or likely to cause 70
death or great bodily harm to another if the person against whom 71
the defensive force is used is in the process of unlawfully and 72
without privilege to do so entering, or has unlawfully and 73
without privilege to do so entered, the residence or vehicle 74
occupied by the person using the defensive force. 75
(3) The presumption set forth in division (B)(2) of this 76
